    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">7. How to Choose -- A Decision Tree</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        {projectCount} projects is a lot. The taxonomy in Section 2 helps narrow the field by philosophy, but most people start with a specific need. Here is a practical decision tree based on the most common questions we see. Each recommendation links to the relevant project page and, where applicable, to head-to-head comparison pages so you can evaluate the tradeoffs yourself.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="rounded-xl bg-ocean-card border border-white/5 p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-bold text-white mb-2">"I want the most mature, battle-tested option"</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400 mb-3">
            Go with <a href="/projects/openclaw/" class="text-biolum hover:text-biolum-light">OpenClaw</a>. At {ocStars} stars and {ocForks} forks, it has the largest community, the most tools, the most documentation, and the most contributors. Its issue count is high ({ocIssues}), but that is a function of scale, not neglect -- the issues-to-stars ratio of {ocIssueRatio}% is moderate. It releases frequently{ocRelease ? ` (latest: ${ocRelease})` : ''} and has daily commits. Nothing else in the ecosystem comes close to its maturity. If you are starting from scratch and have no strong opinions about language or architecture, this is the default choice.
          </p>
