            <a href="/projects/tinyclaw/" class="text-biolum hover:text-biolum-light">TinyClaw</a> ({stars('tinyclaw')} stars, TypeScript) strips the agent to its absolute core. <a href="/projects/microclaw/" class="text-biolum hover:text-biolum-light">MicroClaw</a> ({stars('microclaw')} stars, Rust) does the same in a compiled language. For the truly adventurous, <a href="/projects/bashobot/" class="text-biolum hover:text-biolum-light">BashoBot</a> ({stars('bashobot')} stars, Bash) implements the entire agent loop in shell scripts with zero dependencies beyond curl and jq. It is impractical for production use but an excellent teaching tool for understanding what an AI agent actually does at the system call level.
